TitleFont
(Avondale Membership Automation Overview) 50 792 T

BodyFont
(This note explains, in plain English, what the avondale-n8n processes do and how they support the) 50 760 T
(membership admin work of the club.) 50 744 T

HeadFont
(Terminology) 50 706 T
BodyFont
(- ) 60 680 T
MonoFont
(n8n) 74 680 T
BodyFont
(: the workflow automation tool that runs the club's membership processes.) 100 680 T
(- ) 60 660 T
MonoFont
(Metabase) 74 660 T
BodyFont
(: the reporting dashboard used to view signups, batches, exceptions, and trends.) 134 660 T

HeadFont
(What The Automation Is For) 50 620 T
BodyFont
(The automation exists to reduce manual membership admin after somebody joins or renews through ClubSpark.) 50 596 T
(In practice it does five main jobs:) 50 574 T
(1. captures new membership signups from ClubSpark emails) 70 552 T
(2. refreshes the latest member and contact data from ClubSpark) 70 536 T
(3. combines that information into one operational database) 70 520 T
(4. prepares batches for shoe tags, parent tags, keys, labels, and envelopes) 70 504 T
(5. keeps dashboards and reporting up to date) 70 488 T

HeadFont
(High-Level Functional Description) 50 450 T
BodyFont
(The process starts in ClubSpark. When someone buys a membership, ClubSpark sends a signup notification) 50 426 T
(email and also holds the latest member and contact records for that household.) 50 410 T
(Local n8n workflows regularly pick up those inputs in three ways:) 50 384 T
(- a parser reads the signup notification emails from Gmail) 70 362 T
(- an export workflow pulls the current members list from ClubSpark) 70 346 T
(- another export workflow pulls the current contacts list from ClubSpark) 70 330 T
(Those three inputs are brought together in the local PostgreSQL database, which is the club's operational) 50 304 T
(source of truth for this process. This is where the system works out who signed up, who is paying,) 50 288 T
(what address should be used, and what still needs to be processed.) 50 272 T
(From there, the workflows support the committee's day-to-day membership handling:) 50 246 T
(- new signups are grouped into a processing batch) 70 224 T
(- batch data is turned into printable address labels and DL envelopes) 70 208 T
(- members without a usable postal address can be handled by email instead) 70 192 T
(- manual items can be added when tags or keys are needed outside the normal signup flow) 70 176 T
(- missed signups can be backfilled if ClubSpark shows the membership but the original email was not captured) 70 160 T
(The same local data is then synced to the cloud reporting copy so that Metabase dashboards stay current.) 50 134 T
(This gives the committee visibility of signups, batches, exceptions, and history without making the) 50 118 T
(cloud system the live operational system.) 50 102 T
showpage

